  "identified_domain": "adventure_works",
  "domain_research_summary": "Based on Kyvos best practices and the AdventureWorks analytics intent, the following are industry-standard patterns: (a) multifact schemas for cross-channel sales and financial analytics; (b) rich conformed dimensions to enable drill-across and enterprise reporting; (c) parent-child hierarchies for organizational, employee, department, and account structures; (d) time intelligence KPIs leveraging MDX functions like YTD, QTD, MTD, ParallelPeriod; (e) calculated KPIs for profitability, quota tracking, running totals, ranking, variance, and conditional logic; (f) bridge tables and many-to-many relationships where appropriate (sales_reasons, exchange_rates); (g) star schema within each fact table for performance, but multifact for comprehensive business intelligence.",
