  "gaps_identified": [
    "No explicit date FK between fact tables and date dimension (datekey). Time intelligence can be calculated using date hierarchies but may require indirect mapping in Kyvos DRD.",
    "Product hierarchy: Product table has category and subcategory keys but lacks explicit ProductCategory and ProductSubcategory dimension tables (could be modeled as attributes only).",
    "Geography hierarchy: Geography table exists, but Customer and Reseller tables have their own geo fields; mapping may need custom logic for conformed geography.",
    "Sales reason analytics is possible via sales_reason and sales_reasons bridge tables, but not all facts include explicit salesreasonkey assignments.",
    "Exchange rate analysis is supported via source_currency / destination_currency / exchange_rates, but is not directly linked to sales facts."
  ],
  "domain_reasoning": "The design leverages Kyvos official documentation for parent-child hierarchy creation, alternate path support, custom rollups, MDX KPIs, and semantic model design best practices. All hierarchies are defined using actual warehouse columns. Calculated measures are specified using Kyvos MDX syntax for time intelligence, profitability, variance, and ranking. Multifact schema is chosen due to the presence of multiple sales and finance fact tables with conformed dimensions, supporting rich cross-analysis as required by the business context. Gaps reflect only minor deviations from ideal canonical models, being either implicit in schema (e.g., missing explicit ProductCategory table) or needing custom logic for date/geo conformance across fact tables."
